  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "5c9bef02",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Q4. What is the difference between a function and a function call?\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "Ans 4: A function only acts as a function when it is used to def keyword before declare and parentheses & colon after declare in the \"__main__\" and it contains the groups of instructions or statements to perform.\n",
    "\n",
    "A function call means that we execute the existence function in program and after performing some task it should return something to the function call."
   ]
  },
  {
